## §2 Server vs Client component boundary

**Default**: {{DEFAULT_COMPONENT_TYPE}}

<!-- Server components (App Router default) — no 'use client' unless needed. -->

**When to use `"use client"`**: {{USE_CLIENT_CRITERIA}}

<!-- e.g.:
- Component uses React hooks (useState, useEffect, useRouter from next/navigation, etc.)
- Component uses browser-only APIs (window, localStorage, document)
- Component uses event handlers (onClick, onChange, onSubmit)
- Component uses third-party client-only libraries
-->

**Rules:**
- {{BOUNDARY_RULES}}

<!-- Example:
- Keep components on the server by default. Add `"use client"` at the leaf, not the root — push the boundary as deep as possible.
- Never import a server-only module (e.g., `import { cookies } from 'next/headers'`) into a client component — build fails.
- Interactive wrappers (forms, modals) are client; the data + static content they wrap should stay server.
-->

**Reference files:**
{{BOUNDARY_REFERENCES}}

