## §4 API layer

**API client**: {{API_CLIENT_PATTERN}}

<!-- e.g.:
- A createApiClient() factory at src/api/clients/api-client-factory.ts — returns a typed fetch wrapper or Axios instance per service
- Generated client from OpenAPI spec (openapi-typescript / orval / kubb)
- tRPC client for internal APIs + typed fetch for external
-->

**Route handlers (if any)**: {{ROUTE_HANDLERS}}

<!-- e.g.:
- `app/api/{feature}/route.ts` — for webhook receivers, proxy endpoints, auth callbacks
- Pages Router API routes under `pages/api/`
- No route handlers — Next.js is frontend-only, all APIs are external
-->

**Types from OpenAPI**: {{TYPES_PATTERN}}

<!-- Handwritten under src/api/types/ / generated via codegen pipeline / copied from backend -->

**Rules:**
- {{API_RULES}}

<!-- Example:
- External HTTP calls go through the factory. Never instantiate fetch / Axios directly in a component.
- Base URLs come from `process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_*` (client-visible) or `process.env.*` (server-only).
- TypeScript types match the OpenAPI spec field names character-for-character — no "friendlier" renames.
- Route handlers follow `async function GET/POST/PUT/DELETE(request: NextRequest)` — no default export.
-->

**Reference files:**
{{API_REFERENCES}}

