## §5 Auth & role guards

**Auth pattern**: {{AUTH_PATTERN}}

<!-- e.g.:
- NextAuth.js / Auth.js (v4 or v5) with credentials / OAuth providers
- Clerk / Auth0 / Keycloak SDK
- Custom JWT in httpOnly cookies; middleware.ts enforces session
- Delegated to external identity provider; front-end carries a token
-->

**Role guard pattern**: {{ROLE_GUARD}}

<!-- e.g.:
- useRoles() hook reading session.user.roles
- Middleware.ts does path-based role gating before the component renders
- Server-component-level `getSession()` + redirect if unauthorized
- ProtectedRoute wrapper (rare in App Router)
-->

**Cookie / session storage**: {{SESSION_STORAGE}}

<!-- httpOnly cookies via NextAuth, or a custom cookie + server-validation pattern -->

**Rules:**
- {{AUTH_RULES}}

<!-- Example:
- Gated pages check session in their layout.tsx or page.tsx server component; redirect() unauthorized users.
- Middleware.ts handles coarse-grained path-based gating (e.g., /admin/**); component-level logic handles fine-grained.
- Tokens live in httpOnly cookies — never in localStorage.
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` env vars are reserved for non-sensitive client-visible values; everything else stays server-side.
-->

**Reference files:**
{{AUTH_REFERENCES}}

